race.description: Kick Up For Racing Midway Maiden Handicap
race.comment: WHERE'S MY HALO (1) kept fresh for this and has her hoof on the till from the good gate. Raced ungenerously throughout when an eye-catching second over 1500m here. Blinkers applied today and should stalk the speed and prove hard to hold out. RAWTION (5) resumed over the unsuitable trip when a plugging fifth over 1300m at this track. Can race a touch closer from the good draw and take a hand in the finish. SO REBELLIOUS (6) comes to the provincials for the first time after the two eye-catching runs this preparation. Strong through the line from the outside draw when third over 1400m at Nowra. Value contender. SERPICO (9) back in grade and up in trip when an improved sixth over 1600m at Kembla Grange. Key jockey change and will roll forward and play a leading role.
